Disney has just released an official Trailer for Frozen 2 which is a follow up to the highly successful 2013 animation.   A post shared by Disney (@disney) on Jun 11, 2019 at 4:55am PDT “It’s such a gift that really keeps on giving because people keep on wanting it,” Kristen Bell, who voices Anna in the films, told E! last year of the original’s sustained popularity. “I will do something, anything I’ve been a part of, over and over again if it makes people happy.“ This trailer sees Elsa potentially learning the limits and heights of her powers while on a journey of some sort. Frozen 2 was directed by Jennifer Lee and Chris Buck and is scheduled for a November 2019 release. Watch the official trailer for “Frozen 2” via YouTube below; 